&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operating Department Practitioner/Registered Anaesthetic Nurses – Band 5 Anaesthetics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: East Surrey Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join us at Surrey and Sussex Healthcare NHS Trust as we continue to expand the range of services provided within our theatre complex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 10 operating theatres at our East Surrey site and the Trust has dedicated CEPOD, Trauma and orthopaedics theatres. colorectal and upper GI Surgery, ophthalmic, ENT, Obstetrics, Gynaecology Paediatrics, Dentals, urology, and remote area General anaesthetics. We are continuing to develop our anaesthetic Service and need you to help us!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a UK recognised qualification in anaesthetics and would like to join our friendly team to further develop your skills, we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer an on-going training programme through Surrey University; for student ODP’s and Student Nurses and the successful candidate would be expected to participate in mentoring these students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We positively encourage staff development and have a robust Practise Education team who support Clinical Practice and on-going clinical expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to the development of our staff and have a commitment to additional courses to equip our staffs with the necessary skills in their daily activities through our local Universities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based in Theatre on the East Surrey Hospital site and on occasions you will be requested to provide cover in Crawley Day surgery theatres. We provide 24/7 cover and this requires shift rotation, night duty and an on-call commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further theatre enquiries or an informal visit please contact Principal ODP, Raj Moty, or Practice Development Lead Practitioner, Patrick Dolman-Vesey, on 01737 768511 ext 2644 or email raj.moty@nhs.net, or Theatre Matron, Martin.shaw5@nhs.net ext 1488.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 08/11/2020 (midnight)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 20/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
